=====================================================
                     Geomys
       A Gopher Browser for Macintosh
                   Version 1.1.0
=====================================================

Browse Gopherspace from your classic Macintosh.


About Geomys
-----------

Geomys is a Gopher browser for the Macintosh Plus
and later, running System 6.0.8 or System 7. It
uses MacTCP for networking (also works under Open
Transport's compatibility layer).

It implements RFC 1436 and RFC 4266 with Gopher+
support, handling all 19 Gopher item types. The
browser has a web-style interface with address bar,
back/forward/home, stop/go/refresh, and status bar,
following the Apple Human Interface Guidelines.

On System 7 with Color QuickDraw, Geomys supports
256-color rendering with 14 built-in themes. Color
is detected automatically at runtime.


System Requirements
-------------------

  - Macintosh Plus or later (68000 CPU)
  - System 6.0.8 or later (tested through 7.6.1)
  - MacTCP 2.1 (configured with a valid TCP/IP
    connection; also works under Open Transport's
    MacTCP compatibility layer)
  - 4 MB RAM recommended
  - Network connection (Ethernet or compatible)



Getting Started
---------------

1. Make sure MacTCP is installed and configured in
   your Control Panel. You will need a working TCP/IP
   connection to your network.

2. Double-click the Geomys application to launch it.

3. Geomys opens to a blank page. Set your home page
   in Options > Set Home Page, or type a Gopher URL
   in the address bar and press Return.

4. Click on directory items to navigate deeper into
   Gopherspace. Click on text items to read them.
   Click on binary, image, or sound items to save
   them to disk.

5. Use the Back and Forward buttons (or Cmd-[ and
   Cmd-]) to navigate through your browsing history.

6. Type 7 (search) items open a query dialog. Enter
   your search terms and click OK to see results.

7. To select text, click and drag in the content
   area. Double-click to select a word. Hold Shift
   and click to extend the selection. Press Cmd-C
   to copy. The address bar also supports Cut,
   Copy, and Paste via the Edit menu.

8. Press Cmd-. to cancel an in-progress page load
   or download.

9. To quit, choose Quit from the File menu or press
   Command-Q.


Features
--------

  - Sub-1-second startup
  - All 19 Gopher item types handled: interactive
    browsing, downloads, telnet handoff, and display
  - Gopher+ protocol support: Get Info dialog (Cmd-I)
    showing item attributes, +ABSTRACT display, +SCORE
    search result scoring, +VIEWS content negotiation,
    +ASK interactive forms, bulk attribute fetch
  - Page styles: Text and Icons display modes
    (Options > Page Style)
  - Multi-window browsing with up to 3 simultaneous
    Gopher windows and background loading
  - Binary file downloads to disk via standard save
    dialog with progress display and Stop button
  - Image save with GIF/PNG format detection and
    dimension display
  - HTML tag-stripping renderer for type h items
  - HTML URL extraction with copyable dialog
  - Go menu: Back, Forward, Home, Refresh, Stop,
    Open Location, and browsing history
  - Directory menu with curated Gopher destinations
  - Dynamic stop/go/refresh button right of address
    bar that changes based on browser state
  - Status bar with hover hints showing URIs and
    file info
  - 14 themes including Light, Dark, Solarized,
    TokyoNight, Dracula, Nord, Monokai, Gruvbox,
    Amber CRT, System 7, Green Screen, Classic
  - Find in Page (Cmd-F) with Find Again (Cmd-G)
  - Print support (Cmd-P) via Printing Manager
  - Text selection and copy to clipboard (Cmd-C)
  - Keyboard link navigation with Up/Down arrows
  - Save Page As (Cmd-S) for text and directory pages
  - CP437 character set and Unicode glyph rendering
  - External link dialog with Copy URL button and
    silent browser launch on System 7
  - Telnet connection dialog with Copy Host and
    System 7 app launching for type 8/T items
  - Local page cache with memory-aware sizing for
    instant back/forward navigation
  - MacTCP pre-loaded at startup for fast first
    connect
  - Dynamic directory capacity up to 2,000 items
  - 20 persistent favorites with List Manager dialog,
    keyboard type-ahead, and menu quick-access
  - 8 fonts (Monaco, Geneva, Chicago, Courier,
    New York; Helvetica, Times, Palatino on System 7)
    with independent size selection (9, 10, 12, 14)
  - Horizontal and vertical scrolling
  - Double-buffered rendering eliminates screen flash
  - Apple HIG compliant dialogs (default button
    outlines, Cmd-. cancel, tab field cycling)
  - All preferences saved across launches
  - System 7 Preferences folder support
  - ROM-based SICN/cicn icons for Gopher types and
    navigation buttons (color on Mac II+, mono fallback)
  - Non-blocking TCP connections keep the UI
    responsive during network handshakes
  - Notification Manager: alerts with icon for
    background page loads (System 7)
  - Stationery pad support: save URLs as stationery
    documents that open as new pages (System 7+)
  - System 7 enhancements: modern save dialog,
    Apple Events (odoc/pdoc), MultiFinder
    suspend/resume, Notification Manager alerts for
    background page loads, temporary memory for
    cache, machine type in About dialog
    (all conditional -- System 6 behavior unchanged)


Keyboard Shortcuts
------------------

Geomys is designed for the Apple M0110 and M0110A
keyboards. All shortcuts also work on extended ADB
and USB keyboards.

  Menu Commands
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Command-N       New window
  Command-W       Close active window
  Command-L       Open Location (focus address bar)
  Command-S       Save Page As
  Command-P       Print current page
  Command-D       Add Favorite
  Command-B       Manage Favorites
  Command-I       Get Info (selected link)
  Command-F       Find in Page
  Command-G       Find Again
  Command-C       Copy selected text
  Command-K       Show Clipboard
  Command-Z       Undo (address bar)
  Command-Q       Quit Geomys

  Navigation
  ~~~~~~~~~~
  Command-[       Go back
  Command-]       Go forward
  Command-R       Refresh current page
  Command-.       Stop loading / cancel download
  Return          Navigate to URL (in address bar)
                  Follow selected link (in content)
  Tab             Cycle focus: address bar / content
  Shift-Tab       Cycle focus in reverse

  Content Scrolling
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Up Arrow        Scroll up one row / select
                  previous link (directory pages)
  Down Arrow      Scroll down one row / select
                  next link (directory pages)
  Left Arrow      Scroll left
  Right Arrow     Scroll right
  Page Up         Scroll up one page
  Page Down       Scroll down one page
  Home            Jump to top of page
  End             Jump to bottom of page

  Text Selection
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Click-drag      Select text
  Double-click    Select a word
  Shift-click     Extend selection to click point


Multiple Windows
----------------

Geomys supports up to 3 simultaneous browser windows
(configurable at build time with --max-windows for
systems with more RAM). Each window has its own page
content, browsing history, scroll position, and text
selection.

  Opening Additional Windows:
  - Press Command-N to open a new browser window.
  - New windows open at cascading positions and
    navigate to your home page (or a blank page if
    none is set).

  Switching Between Windows:
  - Click on any window to bring it forward.
  - The Window menu lists all open windows with a
    checkmark on the active window.

  Background Loading:
  - Pages continue loading in background windows
    while you browse in the foreground window.
  - The window title updates when loading completes.

  Closing a Window:
  - Close the window via the close box or Command-W.
  - If a page is loading, you will be asked to
    confirm before closing.
  - After closing the last window, Geomys stays
    running. Use File > New Window or Open Location
    to reopen. Choose File > Quit to exit.

Font and theme changes from the Options menu apply
to all windows. The Window menu count
header shows how many windows are open.


Gopher+
-------

Geomys supports the Gopher+ protocol extension for
servers that advertise enhanced capabilities. Gopher+
features are controlled by the "Gopher+" toggle in the
Options menu (default: off).

  Get Info (Cmd-I):
  Select a link on a directory page using the keyboard,
  then press Cmd-I or choose Get Info from the File
  menu. Geomys fetches attributes from the Gopher+
  server and displays item name, type, server, admin,
  modification date, abstract, and available views.

  Content Negotiation:
  When a Gopher+ item offers multiple content types
  (e.g., text/plain and application/pdf), click
  "Choose View..." in the Get Info dialog to select
  an alternate representation. Geomys sends a Gopher+
  content request for the chosen MIME type.

  Interactive Forms (+ASK):
  Some Gopher+ items support interactive forms with
  text fields, password fields, checkboxes, and radio
  buttons. Click "Fill Form..." in the Get Info dialog
  to fill out and submit the form.

  Bulk Attributes:
  On the first Get Info request for a Gopher+
  directory, Geomys fetches attributes for all items
  in a single request. Cached abstracts are shown in
  the status bar when hovering over links.

  Search Scoring:
  Gopher+ search results may include relevance scores.
  Scores are displayed as a right-aligned column in
  Traditional page style.


Favorites
---------

Geomys can store up to 20 favorites (bookmarks) for
Gopher pages you visit frequently.

  Adding a Favorite:
  1. Navigate to the page you want to bookmark.
  2. Choose "Add..." from the Favorites menu, or
     press Command-D.
  3. Enter a name for the favorite.
  4. Click OK.

  Accessing Favorites:
  - Your 5 most recently added favorites appear
    directly in the Favorites menu for quick access.
  - Choose "Manage..." to see all favorites.

  Managing Favorites:
  1. Choose "Manage..." from the Favorites menu,
     or press Command-B.
  2. Select a favorite in the list.
  3. Use the buttons to Edit, Delete, Move Up,
     Move Down, or Go To.

Favorites and all preferences are saved to a file
called "Geomys Preferences" in the System Folder
(System 7 Preferences folder when available).


Options
-------

The Options menu uses hierarchical submenus for
fonts and themes, with additional items for home
page and display settings.

  Set Home Page
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Configure the URL that loads when you click the
  Home button or choose Go > Home. You can enter
  any gopher:// URL, or check "Use blank page" for
  no home page. The home page is saved to your
  preferences.

  Font (submenu)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Monaco 9pt    Default -- compact monospace
  Monaco 12pt   Larger text, fewer rows
  Courier 10pt  Classic fixed-width alternative
  Chicago 12pt  The classic Mac system font
  Geneva 9pt    Compact proportional font
  Geneva 10pt   Slightly larger proportional font

  Note: Proportional fonts (Chicago, Geneva) use
  per-character positioning to maintain alignment.
  Fixed-width fonts (Monaco, Courier) may render
  slightly faster.

  Theme (submenu)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Choose the color theme for the content area:

  Mono themes (all systems):
    Light         White background, black text
    Dark          Black background, white text

  Color themes (requires Color QuickDraw):
    Solarized Light/Dark
    TokyoNight Day/TokyoNight
    Dracula       Dark purple-accented palette
    Nord          Arctic blue-tinted palette
    Monokai       Dark warm palette, vivid accents
    Gruvbox       Retro earthy palette
    Amber CRT     Amber phosphor CRT aesthetic
    System 7      Macintosh System 7 CLUT colors
    Green Screen  Green-on-black CRT aesthetic
    Classic       1990s web browser colors

  Show Details
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Toggle display of host:port metadata columns on
  directory pages. When unchecked, only the item
  name is shown.

  Status Bar
  ~~~~~~~~~~
  Toggle the status bar at the bottom of all
  windows. The status bar shows hover hints with
  Gopher URIs and file information.

All preferences are saved across launches.


Troubleshooting
---------------

  "Application is busy or damaged"
  Make sure Geomys was copied to the hard drive
  correctly. Try deleting and recopying the file.
  Verify the file type is APPL and creator is GEOM.

  Cannot connect / connection refused
  Verify that MacTCP is installed and properly
  configured in the Control Panel. Check that you
  can reach the remote Gopher server. The default
  Gopher port is 70.

  DNS resolution fails
  Geomys uses its own DNS resolver (default server:
  1.1.1.1). You can also try connecting by IP
  address instead of hostname by typing the address
  directly in the address bar.

  Page appears blank after loading
  Some Gopher servers return empty responses for
  certain selectors. Try navigating to the server's
  root by entering just gopher://hostname in the
  address bar.

  Text appears garbled
  Geomys translates CP437 characters to Mac Roman
  equivalents. If a server uses a different encoding,
  some characters may not display correctly.

  Color themes not available
  Color themes require a Macintosh II or later with
  Color QuickDraw. On monochrome systems (Mac Plus,
  SE, Classic), only Light and Dark themes appear
  in the menu. This is detected automatically at
  startup.

  Downloads fail or are incomplete
  Press Cmd-. to cancel a stalled download. Check
  your network connection and try again. Large files
  may take time on slower connections.

  Window too small for content
  Drag the grow box in the lower-right corner to
  resize the window. Use horizontal scrolling
  (Left/Right arrows) for wide content. Toggle
  Show Details off in the Options menu to reduce
  line width on directory pages.

  Preferences file has no custom icon (System 6)
  On System 6, the Geomys Preferences file may show
  a generic document icon instead of the Geomys icon.
  This is a System 6 Finder limitation -- the icon
  resources are correctly defined and display properly
  on System 7 and later. Try rebuilding the desktop
  (hold Option-Command at startup) if the icon does
  not appear on System 7.


